<br>
To answer you questions quickly, yes he's still broke, yes according to the GM's I've talked to he's supposed to be fixed next patch, and yes he's kos to the mobs in fear.<br>
<br>
The long of it<br>
<br>
The golem is on truespirit faction instead of the denizens(sp) of fear faction.  This causes all fear mobs to attack him soon after he spawns.  We verified this through a FD'd monk near the golems spawn.<br>
<br>
There are a few ways to get around the problem if you want the piece before the patch.<br>
<br>
Find out exactly when he was executed last and clear fear in preparation of his spawning then proceed as normal.<br>
<br>
I heard this on on graffes and it should work.  Give the sproket to the FD'd monk at the golems spawn.  As soon as he spawns give him the gear.  I don't believe the enraged golem will be kos to fear and even if he is I don't' think they will have an easy time killing him.<br>
<br>
The easy(so pissed about the deal you don't feel like dealing with him anymore)  have the aforementioned monk CON the golem at spawn and /report him then petition.  Me and my guildie both received the oil via this method since the mob has been bugged (epic'ed on Christmas day).<br>
<br>
I hope this clears things up, so yes the GM's are VERY aware of the problem with the golem and they are admitting that it's a bug.  I will post the SS of the tell from the GM if anyone wants to see it.<br>
<br>
